{"TopicId":171688,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"\u0026#039;Battery power is better using Microsoft Edge\u0026#039;?","CreatedByName":"Chel","CreatedById":176173,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-05T04:28:09Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Chel","CreatedById":176173,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-05T04:28:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello. While researching/procrastinating today I came across a battery saving area on Microsoft. It says:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EUse Microsoft Edge for browsing.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E Tests show that when browsing with Microsoft Edge, your battery lasts 36-53% longer per charge than when browsing with Chrome, Firefox, or Opera on Windows 10\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nI am wondering how they \u0027tested\u0027 this, and if it is actually true. I do have Edge on my computer, but don\u0027t use it as every couple of minutes it says \u0027a file was reset because it had an asset that wasn\u0027t working\u0027 or something like that. And I haven\u0027t really noticed any difference in battery usage when using Edge instead of Chrome, so is the claim of \u0027Using Edge saves battery\u0027 true?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-05T05:01:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni like computers that plug into the wall.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-05T15:50:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can pretty much ignore anything that says \u0022Tests have shown\u0022 if they don\u0027t cite the tests themselves.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEspecially if it\u0027s a company telling you that their product did the best.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"0111narwhalz","CreatedById":110660,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-05T16:55:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo be fair, Chrome is far from a lightweight browser, and Edge might have the, ah,\u00A0\u003Cem\u003Eedge\u003C/em\u003E\u00A0on the others due to closer OS cooperation. However, I doubt the gains cited are anything but outliers.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-05T18:24:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirefox \u0026gt; Chrome \u0026gt; Edge\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-05T19:02:31Z\u0022 title=\u002203/05/2018 07:02  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 5, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Guest\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nuke","CreatedById":10883,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-05T18:40:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310774\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171688\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520265024\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022179753\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Geonovast\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Geonovast said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can pretty much ignore anything that says \u0022Tests have shown\u0022 if they don\u0027t cite the tests themselves.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEspecially if it\u0027s a company telling you that their product did the best.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou cant even trust third party reviewers anymore.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nin a capitalist society, advertising is propaganda.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-05T18:48:21Z\u0022 title=\u002203/05/2018 06:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 5, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Nuke\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-06T06:34:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310415\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171688\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520224089\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176173\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The_Cat_In_Space\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/4/2018 at 10:28 PM, The_Cat_In_Space said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTests show that when browsing with Microsoft Edge, your battery lasts 36-53% longer...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhether or not it\u0027s true, I don\u0027t care.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo matter how much longer the battery lasts, even if it was days, it still means you have to use Edge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean, if they offer you a single dollar or a billion, it\u0027s still not enough to stick your head in a woodchipper.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-06T08:18:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310925\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171688\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520275220\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002210883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nuke\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Nuke said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyou cant even trust third party reviewers anymore.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nin a capitalist society, advertising is propaganda.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are good reasons why ofcom doesn\u0027t allow even mentioning of brands.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310913\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171688\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520274295\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166583\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022dundun92\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, dundun92 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirefox \u0026gt; Chrome \u0026gt; Edge\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d say :\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nReliability :\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nChrome =\u0026gt; Firefox\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMemory usage (as low as possible) :\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirefox \u0026gt; Chrome\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMicrosoft Edge is, well, I won\u0027t talk much, I haven\u0027t used it and I won\u0027t use it unless someone wants to dodge the\u00A0NoScript and HTTPS Everywhere on my laptop\u0027s Firefox.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310415\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171688\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520224089\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176173\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The_Cat_In_Space\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 05/03/2018 at 11:28 AM, The_Cat_In_Space said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTests show that when browsing with Microsoft Edge, your battery lasts 36-53% longer per charge\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEven more true with a very dim monitor, regardless of browser. If you want your laptop to last whole night observing, don\u0027t forget to dim it down. And airplane mode.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-06T08:21:51Z\u0022 title=\u002203/06/2018 08:21  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 6, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by YNM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-06T17:03:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223311391\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171688\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520324327\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMicrosoft Edge is, well, I won\u0027t talk much, I haven\u0027t used it and I won\u0027t use it unless someone wants to dodge the\u00A0NoScript and HTTPS Everywhere on my laptop\u0027s Firefox.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can\u0027t use edge even if I wanted to... I run Win 7.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}